caption: I constantly come getting some food here. I enjoyed the rapid service and well made food. Keep up the good work.
I tried this spot in the past with my friend and I am obsessed ever since. I love the excellent vibes and flavorful dishes and beverages. Keep it up.

two days ago was our first time we visited this excellent restaurant. But It is no doubt not the last. We passed a splendid evening with the good service, with the finest  meal and booze and with the friendly cost. We will no doubt go back there in a short time.
I love this restaurant a lot. theres a friendly feeling. The cuisine is superb. the service is dynamic and the stuff is very professional. The price is modest. very much recommend.
I had a superb time at this spot. We enjoyed the excellent atmosphere and the food. The waiters were super attentive. I’m content we eventually managed to visit this restaurant.
This place obviously knows how to satisfy their clients. Always with a super friendly approach. The food is conveniently priced, regularly fresh and neat.
Food is delicious and packed very well. the service is great as well. Give this restaurant a try, you'll not regret anything swear
I really love the dishes and service, fantastic location close to my apartment. The workers are always super nice. Will visit here again.
they close by 9pm idk why it says 11pm, we ordered through their website and paid, only to find out it’s closed. smh.

Delicious! Hubby and I shared the mixed kebab plate along with the appetizer sampler plate. Amazing customer service. Don't leave without wrapping up your meal with a piece (or 5) of one of their yummy homemade baklava  along with some Turkish tea. We will definitely be back.
Had a excellent experience here with my wife. The food comes quick and the service is just good. Prices are affordable.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH TUBA NOB HILL! It's almost 2 weeks now you been feeding me a meal a day and I'm very grateful! 😇😇😇😇😇😇😇😇😇😇 😇I am not the only one either...
The place serves large portions and for convenient pricing. friendly employees. Will visit again.
Delicious food, my favorite is Beyti Kebap, very friendly staff, reasonable prices, highly recommended, if you snooze, you lose.. 😋❤️🙏

I meet with friends this great spot from time to time! This is my favorite place to dine.  I visit this place routinely. The food is very tasty, the staff is polite and the prices are affordable. I like being in this spot to have a rich supper.
The food here is amazing. I’ve always gotten the chicken kebab plate and it’s super delicious
Delicious, authentic, and quick 😁

I sent my friends to this place with my warmest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The dishes they serve are appetizing and the team is efficient and cooperative. Whenever we eat in this place we enjoy a delightful evening.  I recommend this place with pleasure.
A preferred place for quality Turkish food. Came in on a Thurs.

Some of the absolute best Turkish food I have EVER had. Practically deserves a poem instead of a normal review. The eggplant and tomato sauce appetizer with bread - superb. The lentil soup - superb. The mixed grill - perfection. The kinafa …
Great service,great food,good price!!!
turkish food and the scene here is excellent. Really nothing but good experiences here. Prices are decent.
Nice and cozy place and food is better than most other Turkish restaurants in sF
Great service, delicious breakfast!
Great food and decent service, pricy though.
The worst turkish food I’ve ever tasted
Tasty, well prepared and served authentic Turkish cuisine!
My favorite spot for quality Turkish food. One of the best spots of its kind in the area. The staff was friendly and observant. Prices were fair.
My top place for Turkish food. Nice place to meet and catch up with family. There was fast and courteous service. It has a nice interior.

Yummy food in a very unassuming location. Musakka was a bit too cheesy but the eggplant, squash and potatoes were assembled and baked perfectly. Very not busy on  Tuesday night. Wine selection was reasonable. Too bad we went for dinner, would have liked to try their Turkish coffee. Next time will try for a day time meal. :)
An absolute delight.
One of my preferred places for quality turkish food. This location is absolutely outstanding. Looking forward to returning with my coworkers. Mood here reminds me of Colorado Springs area.

One of my favorite restourant in sf. Foods are always good. Nice service.

Why do people smoke weed when there is food like this in San Francisco!  Best Turkish food I've had in a while.  For vegans, carnivores, grass fed, gluten free, halal but not sure about organic people.  This is a new branch opened in 2017, …
turkish food... awesome. Super place to meet and chat with coworkers. Service treated us so nice. The bill was good for what you get.

From the moment I entered this establishment, I was sold. The service was amazing. The food: impeccable. We ordered so many mezzos, you can't go wrong. I also ordered the shrimp as my entree, and the garlic sauce compliments it very well. Just go here, you'll love it
A favorite place for tasty turkish food. Good place to relax and unwind.  Service treated us so nice. Bring your hunger - portions are large.
A favorite location for turkish food. Very appetizing. The staff was very helpful and welcoming. This place has a great atmosphere.
Very bad

I always have the best experience here. All of the staff go out of their way to make sure you are accommodated for. THE FOOD is beyond amazing. The entrees, desserts, and drink selection are all so yummy. They marinate the lamb chops for like three days. Like butter 🤤🤤
Amazing food! Unexpected pleasure.  Great find.
Good lamb-beef wrap, but the lavash falls apart by the time you get to the end. Messy, but still finger-licking good. Great baklava, needs to ice cream.
Some of the best Mediterranean food I've ever had. A win.
Excellent food, fast service, and the seating is packed like sardines
Perfect turkish food! Tastes like in istanbul

Great food. Really friendly staff that helped us with understanding the foods we didn't recognize on the menu. We came hungry for a late dinner and left very satisfied. I had the falafel salad with goat cheese inside the falaffels.  Very tasty.
Amazing food. Had the lentil soup, best lentil soup I've ever had. Had falafels and hummus, also arguably best I've had. Great spot for vegetarians and vegans alike. Check this place out.
Great food. Lentil soup is one of the best I've had. Falafel and hummus bowl is great. Really friendly staff and great experience. I look forward to coming back and trying out more items on the menu!
Great food, very friendly and helpful staff. Would definitely visit again.
Best place in town!
Lovely people and amazing food!! Loved it!
The food was authentic as well as the ambiance.  We felt like we were in Istanbul. An excellent evening.
Best Mediterranean menu in the city!!!!
New Tuba Express Gyro ...

Great pasta, and very warm attention.

Luisa's is truly a treasure! Italian food as it is supposed to be by a true Italian. Luisa is up at 6 a.m. daily, making her meatballs, pasta and all other dishes fresh just for us. I've been to Italy and Luisa's food is truly authentic.  I …
Awesome! Met Louisa (86 y/o) very warm and welcoming! Delicious pizza!
Great restaurant, really good plates.. and Luisa makes you feel at home. Buenísimo!!!
Delicious manicotti, bruschetta and specially the tiramisu, the best I've tried here in SF!!
Fresh Italian food.  A must for your list of places to visit.
Wonderful food great atmosphere at good prices
Good food, fair prices.  Only been there once for dinner.
Good place

I came here last Tuesday and left somehow disappointed. My spaghetti bolognese wasn't bad but the pasta did not taste as fresh as I would expect. This wasn't a big problem because the sauce was so delicious to make it up. I'll probably give this place another shot when I am nearby but probably won't come here unless is very convenient.

The restaurant was empty a bit strange but my girlfriend took spaghetti bolognese and it was delicious. For my part I took a pizza and it wasn't good at all. No taste. Really disappointed. The server was fine with us.

Such a cute little authentic place. Server was so nice and helpful on choosing our entrée. Pasta is homemade and delicious, the only thing I was not a fan of was the cannelloni, it was too sweet. Great place to eat.
Great food and Luisa is very friendly, you feel like you came to a family dinner
Underwhelming food. Doesn't seem like a lot of people go here now. Which might explain why the food didn't seem as fresh. And I saw a rat.

Wow I was super disappointed. Pretty pricey and just wasn't worth it. Ended up being almost 100 dollars for bland food.  We walked into an empty restaurant except for a family sitting in the corner.  Ordered the caprese, the house specialty …
Authentic Italian food. The environment is amazing what is even more amazing is the host.  A must visit for San Francisco.
Very fresh-tasting italian food. The chianti was very good too. Immediate seating on a tuesday at 730 pm, pretty laid back.

Luisa is super friendly and the food is AMAZING! We had the cannelloni di carne and the pollo alla piemontese. The cannelloni was the best Italian food I've ever had and we've been to Italy. Also they don't have a kids menu, but …

Phenomenal food & dining experience. Wonderful getting to know Luisa! : )  Three of us delighted in:  Margarita pizza Special seafood stuffed calamari & squid ink pasta Two sauce gnocchi Tiramisu  Magnfico
Most amazing dining experience. Pasta is amazing and conversation with Luisa is a must.
Luisa's moved to California St on Nob Hill, but the food is still fantastic. True, honest Italian food. Luisa's Tiramisu is to die for.
Great Italian food in a great location.  The woman who owns it is very charismatic and friendly, and made one of the best seafood and squid ink pasta I've ever eaten.
Very good food. Service and atmosphere were also good

I can deal with bossy and nosy waiters but the food was just atrocious. I strongly recommend heading to "Jackson Fillmore Trattoria" instead.  I had a glass of Montepulciano red wine, which smelled like vinegar and was full of sediment. My main course was pappardelle with lamb; the pasta was ok but the meat was tough and sinewy.
